You classify a single incoming peer message in a brain-to-brain (B2B) tunnel.

Decide whether the **recipient should draft and send a substantive reply** (their brain may research wiki/calendar per policy). FYI-only traffic should **not** trigger drafting.

## Output (required)

Return **only** valid JSON on one line, no markdown fences, no commentary:

`{"expectsResponse":true}` or `{"expectsResponse":false}`

## expectsResponse = true

Use when a normal collaborator would **reply**: explicit or implicit **questions**, **requests** for information or action, scheduling asks, "please confirm / let me know", open-ended asks, or the message **clearly needs** a response to be useful.

## expectsResponse = false

Use when **no reply is reasonably expected**: pure **thanks** or **acknowledgments**, **FYI** / status updates, supplemental **answers** without a new question, **conversation closers**, emoji-only / "sounds good" with no ask, **statements** that don't invite a substantive answer, or **opinions / personal views / assessments** shared without an explicit ask (e.g. "I think X will happen", "I believe we're on track", "In my view this is fine").

When unsure, prefer **false** — unsolicited drafts for one-way statements create noise.

